column10: My mentality and how I was raised makes managing my money easier.

column8: Money means being able to survive

Money is something that drives me but not in a way of greed but I strive to create generational wealth so that my future family does not ever have to worry if they want to attend college or learn a trade or start a business.
column10: Making it a point to look at your spending frequently; autopaying regular bills that amounts don’t change; automate money being invested in the S&P 500 and into HYSA. Being honest and open with my partner about finances
column12: Not make any large purchases until all bills are paid for the month and in savings. Having snacks at home so when you want a treat you don’t have to spend $ to get it.
